[EXCERPT:HandleLinearStiffness]


While using Ctrl +  Right Click while Simulating in the Physics Asset Tool, this value defines how rigidly the Physics Body keeps its Position in relation to the mouse cursor. A low value will result in the Physics Body continuing to fall. A high value will lock the Physics Body to the cursor.

With a low Handle Linear Damping value and a low Handle Linear Stiffness, you will not be able to affect the position of the Physics Body.

[VAR:ToolTipFullLink]
Engine/Physics/PhysicsAssetEditor/Properties#physicsassettoolproperties
[/VAR]

[/EXCERPT:HandleLinearStiffness]




[EXCERPT:HandleAngularDamping]



[/EXCERPT:HandleAngularDamping]




[EXCERPT:HandleAngularStiffness]

While using Ctrl +  Right Click while Simulating in the Physics Asset Tool, this value defines how rigidly the Physics Body keeps its rotation. A low value here will allow the Physics Body more freely rotate (slowed by Angular Damping). Higher values will lock the Physics Body's rotation while interacting with Ctrl + Right Click.

![](PhAT_AngularStiffness.png)

 [VAR:ToolTipFullLink]
Engine/Physics/PhysicsAssetEditor/Properties#physicsassettoolproperties
[/VAR]

[/EXCERPT:HandleAngularStiffness]




[EXCERPT:InterpolationSpeed]

While in Simulating in the Physics Asset Tool, this defines how quickly the Physics Body you are interacting with using Ctrl + Right Click will track towards the mouse. Lower values will gently move the Physics Body, while higher values will snap it around.
[/EXCERPT:InterpolationSpeed]




[EXCERPT:PokeStrength]

The strength in newtons applied during a "ctrl + left  click" poke during simulation. For most things, the default 100 newtons will not give much of a reaction. For humanoid characters 1500 newtons is a good slap. 15000 newtons is a solid hit with blunt weapon of some sort. Above that and the reaction is like getting hit with a vehicle.

[VAR:ToolTipFullLink]
Engine/Physics/PhysicsAssetEditor/Properties#physicsassettoolproperties
[/VAR]

[/EXCERPT:PokeStrength]




