[/EXCERPT:bShowNamesInHierarchy]




[EXCERPT:ConstraintDrawSize]

The crosses that visualize where the constraints are located are set to be the same size no matter how far from the camera they are. This can lead to them being hidden if the camera is too close to the skeletal mesh, as the crosses appear to retract into the mesh. Or if the camera is too far, all the crosses will become an overlapping mess.

![](PhAT_RTT_ConstraintScale.png)

Increasing this value will scale the crosses up, while reducing it will scale them down.

[VAR:ToolTipFullLink]
Engine/Physics/PhysicsAssetEditor/Properties#physicsassettoolproperties
[/VAR]

[/EXCERPT:ConstraintDrawSize]
